check.output-format:
Emit to stdout:

```
SUCCESS
Document: {absolute path in the global extern store}
Repo: {org/repo}
Topic: {topic}
Reused: {true if prior catalog research was returned without cloning; false otherwise}
Clone: {".extern/{org-repo}/ (left in place)" or "not cloned (reused existing)"}
Key findings: {1-2 sentences, or "pattern not present in repo"}
```

Present to the user:

## Scout Complete

**Document**: {global store path}
**Repo**: {org/repo} · **Topic**: {topic}

{1-2 sentence summary of the key findings with clone-relative
citations, or the negative finding}

Then offer next actions:
- Study another topic in the same repo
- Compare this external pattern against our internal approach
  (Comparative Matrix)
